Plot:
After busting down the flesh traders in Noman and saving his wife Nargis[N 1], Sameer leads a peaceful life with Nargis, who becomes depressed after the Noman incident. Deepak, Sameer's best friend tells him that he has decided to send his brother's daughter Nandini to an adoption centre as his brother and sister-in-law have died in an accident and he can not take care of her due to his work, but Sameer and Nargis oppose that and adopt Nandini as their daughter, beginning a happy life.

However, their happiness is short-lived when Nandini's classmate Basheshwar "Bachchu" Thakur forces her classmate Seema to accept his love, but Seema rejects him. Enraged, he kidnaps Seema, along with Nandini (who tried to save her). Sameer, Nargis and Seema's family file a missing complaint, but the cops don't take the case seriously as Bachchu is the grandson of a powerful landlady named Sheela Thakurji, and advise them to stay away from the case.

Sameer learns that Nandini and Seema are brutally injured, where Seema becomes the lone survivor, but Nandini dies of the injuries. Sameer and Nargis are shattered by Nandini's death and Sameer leaves to seek vengeance against Bachchu and Sheela Thakurji.
